    <summary>Convert natural language to safe POSIX shell commands using local LLMs</summary>
    <description>
cmdai is a single-binary Rust CLI tool that converts natural language descriptions
into safe POSIX shell commands using local LLMs. The tool prioritizes safety,
performance, and developer experience with Apple Silicon optimization via MLX framework.

Features:
- Instant startup - Single binary with fast cold start
- Local LLM inference - Optimized for performance
- Safety-first - Comprehensive command validation framework
- Zero dependencies - Self-contained binary distribution
- Multiple backends - Extensible backend system (MLX, vLLM, Ollama)
- Cross-platform - macOS, Linux, Windows support
    </description>
